datablock.item: The structure is well resolved in spite of significant anion and solvent disorder. The disordered BF4 anion has been modelled using a single boron atomic site, a set of four equal occupancy, partially occupied [54.8(9)%] fluorine atomic sites and a spherical shell of electron density centred on the boron atomic site of radius 1.38 angstrom and containing the electron density of the remaining 1.81(3) unresolved fluorine atoms. This composite model provided a significantly improved fit to the observed data.
